1. e4 { Notes by Dr. Tarrasch.}  1... e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 a6 4. Bxc6 { If White
can do this with impunity,  (  as indeed seems likely  )  , a6 would be a
pointless move.}  4... dxc6 5. Nc3 Bc5 6. d3 Bg4 7. Be3 Qd6 8. Bxc5 Qxc5 9. Qd2
{ !}  9... Bxf3 { ? A grievous misjudgement, bringing disadvantage to Black. f6
was indicated.}  10. gxf3 Ne7 11. O-O-O Ng6 12. Qe3 { !}  12... Qxe3+ { Not
good because it strengthens White's center. But after 12...Qe7 Black could not
have castled Q side on account of Qa7, whereas castling K-side would have been
dangerous on account of the open g-file. Black is paying the penalty of his
mistake on the 9th move.}  13. fxe3 Rd8 14. Ne2 f6 15. Rhg1 Kf7 { Castling was
preferable.}  16. Rdf1 Rhe8 17. Ng3 Nf8 18. f4 c5 { The game is untenable.
Black tries to provide against 19 fxe5 Rxe5 20 d4 followed by e5; but there is
even worse to come.}  19. Nh5 g6 20. fxe5 { ! To take the Knight would allow a
mate in 2.}  20... Rxe5 21. Nxf6 Kg7 22. Rf2 h5 23. Nd5 c6 24. Nf4 c4 25. Rfg2
Rd6 26. h4 cxd3 27. cxd3 Kf7 28. Rg5 Rxg5 29. Rxg5 Rf6 30. e5 Rf5 31. Rxf5+
gxf5 32. d4 { Better than Nxh5 which would be good enough too.}  32... Ke7 33.
Kd2 c5 34. Kd3 cxd4 35. exd4 Kd8 36. d5 Kd7 37. Kd4 Kc7 38. b4 Kd7 39. Kc5 Kc7
40. d6+ Kd7 41. Kd5  1-0

